move over paris tokyo will join you in the ranks 
of cities with eightdigit phone numbers 
nippon telegraph and telephone corp said tuesday that the change 
from sevendigit phone numbers in tokyo will take place jan 1 
1991 subscribers will add a 3 at the beginning of their sevendigit 
numbers 
the national telephone utility said a shortage of exchange 
numbers began showing up in 1981 as demand increased for facsimile 
and microcomputer communications on top of demand for regular 
telephone lines 
some eightdigit phone numbers were given to pocket pagers in 
1987 and in 1988 some new subscribers for regular phones received 
eightdigit numbers ntt said but by early 1991 the shortage will 
be acute 
unlike in france which has had eightdigit local phone numbers 
throughout the country for several years the change in japan will 
affect only phone numbers in tokyo a city of 12 million people 
