<TEXT>
it began with a pair of pink flamingos 
a decade later dick and janes spot has become a work of art 
festooned with 1600 bicycle reflectors 20000 bottle caps and a 
6foot hand that once belonged to a fortune teller the home of 
artists dick elliott and jane orleman is their largest art work 
art over the years was a very serious thing and we feel this is 
a more fun point of view said jane 47 we dont try to 
represent the angst of the world we try to alleviate it 
located on a quiet street in this university town of 11000 
residents dick and janes spot which doubles as their residence 
has been surprising and delighting passersby since 1979 
a combination roadside attraction and fullsize playhouse the 
spot is an everchanging work with sunlight reflecting different 
colors from each reflector and more than 100 silver bicycle wheels 
whirling in the wind the bottle caps rust and the garden changes 
through the seasons 
the couple recently received a 2500 grant from art matters 
inc a new york city foundation to install lights in the yard so 
darkness can no longer obscure the sights 
they bought the 100yearold frame house for 18000 when it was 
a decrepit wreck in 1978 and shortly after received a pair of pink 
flamingos from janes mother 
they soon began adding things over the years about 30 artists 
have contributed carvings sculpture and other pieces the 100 
separate works include carved heads a sculpture using a huge fish 
net and a brick fountain in the shape of a heart known as the heart 
of washington that is a pun on ellensburgs location in the center 
of the state 
its sort of turning into a private museum for folk art said 
dick 43 weve become a humane society for lost art 
the most popular work is a statue of a man with a camera for a 
face and flashcubes for eyeballs dick said 
its a camerafaced tourist he said people really like 
that one 
there is a guest book outside the fence with a sign saying what 
is this place above it 
thats the most frequently heard question dick said 
now included on tour bus stops the spot is surrounded by a 
wooden fence the major works are in the front and back yards and 
can be viewed from the sidewalk 
we are not open to the public dick said we dont want 
people coming into the yard 
the couple met when both were art students at central washington 
university in ellensburg 
when they arent replacing the bicycle reflectors or fixing the 
rotating wheels they operate the spot janitorial co which cleans 
businesses in the area 
they work parttime running the business with the rest of the 
time devoted to art 
dick makes paintings using thousands of small reflectors 
he has a show opening at the desonsaunders gallery in chicago 
another opening soon at the richard gasperi gallery in new orleans 
and has had shows in the seattle area 
one of his paintings requiring 25000 reflectors will be 
installed at the university of washington this fall and they just 
received a fellowship from the bellevue art museum 
im the only person i know of using reflectors as a painting 
medium dick said adding he had to search for years before 
finding a factory to produce the reflectors 
jane also is a painter although generally with actual paint 
she also has created several of the sculptures in the yard 
the orlemans married 18 years have no intention of selling the 
house 
its home jane said 
