more than 20 trade unions backed by opposition political parties 
joined in calling the 24hour general strike the unions represent 
bandladeshs 15 million industrial and railroad workers and demand 
the government nearly double the minimum wage from the equivalent of 
25 a month to 44 they also want allowances pegged to the cost of 
