<TEXT>
hyundai auto canada inc officially opened 
its mammoth car assembly plant here tuesday by announcing it will 
build another plant nearby to make body parts 
quebec premier robert bourassa who was on hand for the opening 
said the quebec government will grant the korean carmaker 59 
million us towards the new 1444million parts plant it is 
scheduled to begin stamping parts such as fenders hoods and roofs 
in october 1990 
the assembly plant opened to the applause of about 2000 
employees and visitors produces the sonata midsize sedan 
the first sonata rolled out jan 12 and hyundai is making about 
500 a week full production of about 2000 cars a week or 100000 a 
year is expected to be reached in 1991 said hyundai spokesman greg 
young 
the bromont plant about 55 miles east of montreal was built at 
a cost of 3877 million with quebec and canadian federal 
government subsidies of 131 million it employs about 800 but that 
figure is expected to grow to 1200 once full production is reached 
